A man who 'preyed' on women online and broke dozens of hearts across state lines is today facing charges of stealing from his conquests to fund his casanova lifestyle.

Ray Holycross, 29, who is also said to go by the names Ray Parris, Ray Cross and Ray Tompson, is accused of defrauding some of the 38 women he seduced after meeting them over the internet.

Police say he is suspected of plotting a journey across the US from the Midwest to Portland, Florida and Texas using dating websites to meet women he could move in with and steal from in.

