He is accused of various offenses including withdrawing $1,000 from the bank of one ex and stealing electronic goods from iphones to laptops.

He is due to be arraigned today on one charge of theft, accused of stealing the camera of former partner Theresa Bridgegroom, of Mishawaka, Indiana.

Holycross is also wanted in Oregon on two counts stemming from an identity theft charge.

Police say many more women have come forward claiming he preyed on them through online dating sites and fooled them into believing he was in love before taking their belongings.

According to ABC there are 38 allegations in total.

'I think he relies on girls that he meets on the Internet to provide him with what he needs to get through life,' Lt. Michael Budreau of the Medford Police Department in Oregon said in August.

